Subject: Re: bastard motor?

>From: "Kevin Guarnotta" <kguarnotta(-at-)usa.net>
>Date: Tue, 24 Sep 2002 08:31:16 -0400
>
>i have heard this term thrown around a lot...what exactly does it mean.

The aluminum/magnesium alloy that VW used in their engines was very
eager to do its job.  Some of it was so eager that it jumped out of
the smelter and ran off to make engine cases without the blessing of
the VW foundry operators.  This is where "bastard" engines come from. 

:)

